  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Disease modifying therapies (DMT) are widely used for children and adolescents with MS.
      Nonetheless, many pediatric patients continue to relapse and therefore require changes in
      therapy. We designed this research study to learn more about medication use in children and
      adolescents with MS. We are also interested in learning what a behavioral feedback
      intervention can tell us about adherence to medicine. Finally, we hope this research project
      will inform the way we provide clinical care for children and adolescents with MS.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
